Ranger Help for: general
========================

SUMMARY:
Rangers are the guardians of the wild places of Darkwind. They serve
Gaia, the spirit of the earth, and draw their strength from the natural
world. Equally at home stalking through deep forests or scaling frozen
mountain passes, Rangers are skilled survivalists, trackers, and fighters.

HOW RANGERS PLAY:
Rangers are a self-sufficient class built around three pillars:

  SURVIVAL - Craft your own gear from the land. Harvest wood, make rope,
  forge tools, skin animals for hide, mix herbs into salves and poisons,
  carve bows and arrows. You can camp anywhere in the wilderness.

  COMBAT - A mix of melee and ranged fighting. Rangers use bows for
  ranged attacks (quickshot, heartshot, furyfire, longfire) and blades
  for close combat (strike, gash, impale, naturestrike). Circle your
  opponents for positional advantage, or ambush from concealment.

  NATURE MAGIC - Channel Gaia's power through meditation, wrath,
  winter's bite, and seasonal flux. Protect yourself and heal with
  essence of the land and nature's protection. At high levels, become
  Gaia's living incarnation.

TERRAIN SYSTEM:
Every Ranger chooses a primary and secondary terrain. These affect
everything: combat damage, spell costs, cooldown times, and which
animals you can bond with. Your primary terrain gives the biggest
bonuses (+20%), your secondary less (+10%). Choose them to match
where you like to adventure.

COOLDOWNS:
Ranger abilities recover in separate categories. Combat maneuvers,
crafting, fieldwork, travel, camp work, and companion commands each
have their own rhythm. Heavy recovery skills such as rest and camp
tend still require a broader pause before other Ranger abilities.

ANIMAL COMPANIONS:
Rangers can attract and bond with animal followers from the wild.
Your companion fights alongside you, can be trained with tricks,
and is unique to your terrain. But be careful - each Ranger has a
limited number of followers in their lifetime. If too many die,
no more will come.

